But who did bid thee join with us?Macbeth.He needs not our mistrust, since he deliversOur offices and what we have to doTo the direction just.Then stand with us.The west yet glimmers with some streaks of day:Now spurs the lated traveller apaceTo gain the timely inn; and near approachesThe subject of our watch.Hark! I hear horses.[Within]  Give us a light there, ho!Then 'tis he: the restThat are within the note of expectationAlready are i' the court.His horses go about.Almost a mile: but he does usually,So all men do, from hence to the palace gateMake it their walk.A light, a light!'Tis he.Stand to't.It will be rain to-night.Let it come down.O, treachery! Fly, good Fleance, fly, fly, fly!Thou mayst revenge. O slave!Who did strike out the light?Wast not the way?There's but one down; the son is fled.We have lostBest half of our affair.Well, let's away, and say how much is done.